==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: LH
<hw>LH</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biochem.)</fld> <def>An abbreviation for
<sig>luteinizing hormone</sig>, a gonadotropic hormone that is secreted
by the pituitary and stimulates ovulation in female mammals, and
stimulates androgen release in male mammals.</def>
<mark>[Acronym]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> luteinizing hormone, interstitial cell-stimulating
hormone.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

